content.description: Sit start on a blocky jug and make a big move up to an awesome pinch. Use some high step trickery to make your way up the challenging vertical face to an easy finish on good holds.
content.location: This boulder is the highest established problem in the upper west and is difficult to see from below. It is accessed via the trail that continues past several boulder problems up and left from The Hole Show. From Queen Bee, continue up and trend right slightly towards a large Juniper tree. Tree Lobster climbs the left arete of a beautifully streaked boulder just above the Juniper tree.Â

content.description: Stand start and make a few extended moves to better holds in the face. Exercise care and delicate footwork off the deck.
content.location: Approximately 15 feet to the right of Tree Lobster on the obvious grips.

content.description: A few large boulders in the Upper west part of the Canyon. This area gets a lot of sun in the morning, and decent shade especially later afternoon. One of the longer approaches but certainly worth it.
